|Example.Comments=The key preposition in this sentence is "az" [from], if the phrase were "tuhfih-i dimukrasi," then the use would be metaphorical, but this is "tuhfih-i AZ dimukrasi," a gift from democracy, or a gift made of democracy. I don't believe this is metaphorical as it.


